d.At once an engaging treatise and a creative gesture, Lovecidal probes the physical and psychic conditions of the world and shows us a society that is profoundly heartsick. Taking up with those who march both as and for the oppressed—who walk with the disappeared to help carry them forward—Trinh T. Minh-ha engages the spiritual and affective dimensions of a civilization organized around the rubrics of nonstop governmental subjugation, economic austerity, and highly technologized military conflict. In doing so, she clears a path for us to walk upon. Along with our every step, the world of the disappeared lives on.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aState-sponsored terrorism. 0aWar and society. 0aWar. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aAsymmetrical War.  aDark Night Policy.  aDarkness.  aHeart.  aLong Lost Love.  aLovecidal.  aPending Ending.  aSuicidal.  aThe Art of War.  aThe Disappeared.  aThe other victory.  aTwin Victories.  aVictory mindset.  aWalking.  aWar Mindset.  aWar Projections.  aWar.  ablank page.  acircle of love.  aculture disappearance.  adisappeared.  adisplaced.  adispossessed.  adissidence.  aeducation.  aempty chair.  aenhanced security.  ahealthcare.  aimage under erasure.  ainternet censorship.  alight.  aliquid ending.  anational security.  anight of becoming.  anight.  aresistance.  asmell of victory.  asuicide of love.  atears and truth.  aultimate protest.  aunderground.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311072902340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823271122zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823271122423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823271122/original  a978-3-11-